file=Brand Studio/muse/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: muse-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical\nstatus: built — inherits from Shared OS (2026-07-15)\nassigned_agent: muse (Brand Studio / Ideation)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\ndate_filled: 2026-07-15\n · p:=Logical artifacts are Python scripts in `Shared OS/logical/` (playbook §13.5). Muse inherits the department-shared `marketing_laws.py`. All dedicated scripts are paywall-blocked pending Route D .md files. This file is the only file in this folder.\n · tb=\| # \| Script \| Source Book 1 \| Book 1 URL \| Source Book 2 \| Book 2 URL \| Route \| · tb=\|---\|--------\|--------------\|------------\|---------------\|------------\|-------\| · tb=\| 1 \| `marketing_laws.py` \| Ries & Trout, *The 22 Immutable Laws of Marketing* (1993) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/22immutablelawso00alri) — FREE \| Cialdini, *Pre-Suasion* (2016) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/presuasionrevolu0000cial) — FREE \| B \| · s(o:Scripts (Shared OS/logical/)=Additional free sources: Pareto (1896), Marshall (1890), Bernays (1928), Campbell (1949), Zipf (1949), Lasswell (1948), Hick (1952), Zajonc (1968), Von Restorff (1933). 10 free books/papers total.\n · tb=\| Script \| Source Book \| Book URL \| Why Muse Needs It \| · tb=\|--------\|------------\|----------\|---------------------\| · tb=\| `marketing_laws.py` \| Ries & Trout + Cialdini + 8 free sources \| See above \| Grounds NAF/ICE rubrics, novelty judgments, and deduplication with distinctiveness, positioning, and category laws \| · tb=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · tb=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| NAF/ICE rubrics — Novelty/Applicability/Feasibility scoring flagged as rubric-based \| ✅ Cleared \| `marketing_laws.py` — `von_restorff_effect` (measurable distinctiveness for Novelty anchor), `law_of_focus` (Applicability: does the idea own a word?), `law_of_the_category` (Feasibility: category creation vs variant) \| · tb=\| deduplication "mechanism-level sameness" — judgment-based \| ✅ Cleared \| `marketing_laws.py` — `von_restorff_effect` (compute distinctiveness score between ideas), `law_of_perception` (are two ideas perceptually different?) \| · tb=\| Divergence Guard triggers — rubric without measurable content \| ✅ Cleared \| `marketing_laws.py` — `law_of_the_category` (is this a new category or a variant?), `law_of_leadership` (first-in-category advantage test) \| · sts:Skills to Script Mapping=- **idea-generation** — imports `marketing_laws.py` (`von_restorff_effect` for novelty scoring, `law_of_the_category` for category-creation ideas)\n- **idea-evaluation** — imports `marketing_laws.py` (`law_of_perception` for deduplication, `law_of_focus` for positioning strength, `pareto_principle` for idea prioritization)\n · tb=\| Script \| Blocked By \| Source Needed \| · tb=\|--------\|-----------\|---------------\| · tb=\| Dedicated creativity research extraction \| Paywalled book \| Creativity research text with measurable constructs (originality/usefulness measures, consensual assessment technique) \| · tb=\| Dedicated Berger STEPPS extraction \| Paywalled book \| Berger, *Contagious* — concept-level spread filter (shared with lena's list; lands in lena's folder at extraction time) \| · sp:Still Pending=These require Route D .md files from paywalled sources before extraction can proceed.\n